to go squirrely on me.

08:17.915 --> 08:19.873
[bleep]!

08:19.917 --> 08:21.875
I think I was a little premature
jumping on the power hammer.

08:21.919 --> 08:24.669
That was a separation.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.379
<i> As I'm drawing</i>
<i> this billet out,</i>

08:26.423 --> 08:29.382
I cannot get the damn thing
to stay.

08:29.426 --> 08:31.593
The ends keep
separating.

08:34.223 --> 08:37.557
I'm forced to re-weld
and lose material,

08:37.601 --> 08:40.769
and re-weld
over and over.

08:40.812 --> 08:42.812
- He doesn't have enough steel
to make a knife.

08:42.856 --> 08:46.983
It's not too late
to start over.

08:47.027 --> 08:48.944
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

08:48.987 --> 08:50.570
<i> - I'm gonna wait for it to get</i>
<i> hot enough to weld,</i>

08:50.614 --> 08:52.697
<i> but I'm kind of putting</i>
<i> my eggs in this basket.</i>

08:52.741 --> 08:57.202
Hopefully we get the canister to
seal up and weld.

08:57.246 --> 08:58.453
- Like, here we go.
- He's got the hammer.

08:58.497 --> 09:00.372
- Here we go.

